{"cursor":"8278","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\n\n'Understanding' (also called '[[intellection]]') is a psychological process\nrelated to an abstract or physical object, such as a person, situation, or\nmessage whereby one is able to think about it and use concepts to deal\nadequately with that object. Understanding is a relation between the knower and\nan object of understanding. Understanding implies abilities and dispositions\nwith respect to an object of knowledge sufficient to support intelligent\nbehavior.\n\nAn understanding is the limit of a conceptualization. To understand something is\nto have conceptualized it to a given measure.\n","linknr":338,"url":"Understanding","recorded":1362901935,"links":44,"instances":["kabbalah","personality_type","story","linguistics","opinion","philosophy"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Cognition","Knowledge","Mental processes","Concepts in epistemology"],"headings":["Examples","Is understanding definable?","Religious perspectives","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/40px-Edit-clear.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/40px-Edit-clear.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/37px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["process","philosophy"],["advice","opinion"],["istp","personality_type"],["understand","story"],["binah","kabbalah"],["meaning","linguistics"]],"members":["binah","istp","understand","meaning","advice","process"],"related":["Psychological","Process_(philosophy)","Person","Message","Concept","Concept","Prediction","Expla